title: Rory O'Carroll
text:
Rory O'Carroll (born 30 November 1989) is a <a href="Gaelic%20football">football</a>er and <a href="Hurling">hurler</a> with <a href="Dublin%20GAA">Dublin</a> and <a href="Kilmacud%20Crokes">Kilmacud Crokes</a>. He lined out as the full back on the Dublin senior football team. He is the brother of inter-county footballer and hurler <a href="Ross%20O%27Carroll">Ross O'Carroll</a>, inter-county hurler Bill O’Carroll and Oisin O'Carroll. Rory O'Carroll made his debut for Dublin against <a href="Kerry%20GAA">Kerry</a> in March 2009.
Playing career.
O'Carroll holds two All-Ireland medals. In 2009, he won an <a href="All-Ireland%20Senior%20Club%20Football%20Championship">All-Ireland Senior Club Football Championship</a> winners medal with <a href="Kilmacud%20Crokes">Kilmacud Crokes</a> and in 2010, he won the <a href="All-Ireland%20Under%2021%20Football%20Championship">All-Ireland Under 21 Football Championship</a> with Dublin. He was named on the team chosen as the best 15 players at Under-21 level between 2005 and 2010. O'Carroll won the <a href="Leinster%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">Leinster Senior Football Championship</a> with <a href="Dublin%20GAA">Dublin</a> in July 2011 at <a href="Croke%20Park">Croke Park</a> against <a href="Wexford%20GAA">Wexford</a>. He won the <a href="All-Ireland%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">All-Ireland Senior Football Championship</a> with Dublin in September 2011 against <a href="Kerry%20GAA">Kerry</a> at <a href="Croke%20Park">Croke Park</a>.
Personal.
O'Carroll went to Oatlands in Stillorgan, and is currently a student in <a href="University%20College%20Dublin">University College Dublin</a> (UCD), where he studies French and History and plays for the college GAA teams. He is also well known for engaging in charitable work in Dublin's inner city, in particular Brother Kevin's Capuchin centre in Smithfield. He is also a keen and capable Irish speaker.
